page.title: 10BILLERICAY NW Residential
page.content: { {Houses and Flats { { }The residential area in this part of Billericay consists of older houses (approx. 1930's) and the new estate that is expanding rapidly. The older{houses and bungalows}are mainly detached each with its own well_tended garden back and front. Most of them have{garages. { }The{flats}near the station are four storeys high making them difficult for elderly people and young mothers. Children have no place to play. The new{Queens Park Estate}is a rapidly expanding area of houses and flats built around cul_de_sacs. As land is expensive the gardens are small but the whole estate has been pleasantly landscaped. The estate has no shops except a large{supermarket.
